	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A simple solution would be to do like the 3-in-1s for DS Slot 1 do and flash a boot-able rom to non-volatile memory (like NAND or flash rom) and have it so if the device doesn't see an SD card in the device, it boots from said flash/nand/what have you and acts like a regular GB/GBC game.
<br />
<br />This would allow you to use it with stuff like the SGB and N64 pokemon transfer pack.
<br />
<br />Might be hard to fit that all in a small form factor though...

		

		</td>
